field_label:
The conversation transitions to eliciting and talking about barriers: 
  
1. If the patient has not already determined where to schedule an appointment (their referrals consultation at the health fair should help with this), help the patient figure out where to go. 
  
2. If patient has not scheduled an appointment: 
"What has kept you from scheduling an appointment?" "What would get you to schedule an appointment?" "Do you want my assistance in scheduling an appointment?"  
  
3. If the patient has scheduled but not yet attended the appointment: 
"What may be challenging in attending this appointment?" 
"What may be simple in attending this appointment?" 
  
4. If the patient has attended the appointment: 
"Congratulations!" Technically your role as patient navigator for the study has been fulfilled, but you can offer if they want your assistance for attending a follow up appointment (and if so, write a comment about it)

select_choices_or_calculations: 1, Care coordination | 2, Communication/education | 3, Logistical | 4, Insurance/medical costs | 5, Health promotion | 6, Cultural/religious/spiritual | 7, Work/school | 8, Psychosocial/distress/behavioral | 11, Access to care/system challenges | 12, Coordinating appointments | 13, Health care concerns | 9, None | 10, Other
1, Access to care/system challenges | 2, Coordinating appointments | 3, Health care concerns

field_label:
The conversation now transitions to using motivational interviewing to address the barriers the patient brought up. If the patient brings up a laundry list of barriers, ask the patient which one they want to focus on for the call. The goal is to address the barrier so that the patient feels motivated to make or attend their health care appointment. 
  
The fields below are for you (patient navigator) to log and keep track of the motivational interviewing conversation. 
  
"I'm hearing from you that you are encountering some barriers in getting health care. Let's talk about one of them today and see how we can overcome it."
What is the behavior to change?

select_choices_or_calculations: 1, Precontemplative | 2, Contemplative | 3, Preparation | 4, Action | 5, Maintenance | 6, Relapse

field_label:
The conversation transitions from motivational interviewing to setting SMART goals.  
  
"Given our conversation thus far, what goals about the barrier we discussed or about seeing a doctor can you make for next time we talk?"  
"Can you make this goal specific?"  
Get them to make their goal S.M.A.R.T by asking them questions that help them articulate very specifically how they will achieve their goal. There is room to document their goal on this form.

What is the specific SMART goals? 
SMART = a goal that is specific, measurable, agreed upon, realistic, and time based.

Closing the conversation. 
  
Summarize what you have talked about so far: 
- Appointment status 
- Barriers 
- SMART goal 
  
Ask if they have anything more they would like to talk about. 
  
Plan a date and time for your next follow up phone call.
Date planned for follow-up phone call

Please read the following script to the patient:

"We have a unique program through UM DOCS. If, during the fair, you come to a station and they recommend that you seek follow-up care with a physician, we can pair you up with a student volunteer who can work with you to help you set up an appointment, establish a primary care physician if you don't have one, and even figure out insurance/payment options with you (for example, helping you to obtain a Jackson Card). The volunteer can work with you through phone calls, text messages, e-mail, or whatever communication method is preferable for you so you can work together to achieve your health care goals. We wanted to introduce this program to you at the beginning of the fair so you know more about the program and whether you would be interested in it. You can learn more about this program when you go to the Final Doctor Evaluation Station."

Formulario de Consentimiento para la Navegación del Paciente

"Tenemos un programa único a través de UM DOCS. Si, durante la feria, usted viene a una estación y le recomiendan que busque atención de seguimiento con un médico, podemos emparejarlo con un estudiante voluntario que pueda trabajar con usted para ayudarle a programar una cita, establecer un médico de atención primaria si no tiene uno e incluso buscar opciones de seguro / pago con usted (por ejemplo, ayudarlo a obtener una tarjeta Jackson). El voluntario puede trabajar con usted a través de llamadas telefónicas, mensajes de texto, correo electrónico o cualquier otro método de comunicación que sea preferible para usted, de modo que pueda trabajar en conjunto para lograr sus objetivos de atención médica. Queríamos presentarle este programa al comienzo de la feria para que sepa más sobre el programa y si le interesaría. Puede obtener más información acerca de este programa cuando vaya a la Estación de evaluación final del médico ".

Fòm Konsantman Navigasyon Pasyan

"Nou gen yon pwogram inik nan UM DOCS Si, pandan jis la, ou vini nan yon estasyon epi yo rekòmande ke ou chache swivi swen ak yon doktè, nou ka pè ou ak yon volontè elèv ki ka travay avèk ou nan ede ou etabli yon randevou, etabli yon doktè swen primè si ou pa gen yon sèl, e menm figi soti asirans / peman opsyon avèk ou (pou egzanp, ede ou jwenn yon Jackson Card). Volontè a ka travay avèk ou nan apèl telefonik, mesaj tèks, e-mail, oswa kèlkeswa metòd kominikasyon ki pi preferab pou ou pou ou ka travay ansanm pou reyalize objektif swen sante ou. Nou te vle prezante pwogram sa a ba ou nan kòmansman an nan jis la pou w konnen plis sou pwogram ak si ou ta enterese nan li.Ou ka aprann plis sou pwogram sa a lè ou ale nan Estasyon final Doktè Evalyasyon an. "
